%% Kubeflow Notebook Controller - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Notebook Webhook<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant ODHCtrl as ODH Controller
    participant KFCtrl as KF Controller
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuthServer as OpenShift OAuth Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuthProxy as oauth-proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Notebook as Notebook Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP

    Note over User, Notebook: Flow 1: Notebook Creation with OAuth

    User->>Dashboard: Create Notebook
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: POST Notebook CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-notebook-v1<br/>Auth: K8s CA cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Patched: +oauth-proxy sidecar<br/>+reconciliation lock<br/>+proxy env vars
    K8sAPI-->>Dashboard: Notebook Created

    ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceAccount<br/>Create OAuth Service (443->8443)<br/>Create OAuth Secret<br/>Create Route (Reencrypt)<br/>Create NetworkPolicies<br/>Create trusted-ca ConfigMap
    ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Remove reconciliation lock

    KFCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create StatefulSet<br/>Create Service (8888)

    Note over User, Notebook: Flow 2: User Accessing Notebook (OAuth Mode)

    User->>Router: GET https://{notebook-route}<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Router-->>User: 302 Redirect to OAuth
    User->>OAuthServer: Login with OpenShift credentials<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    OAuthServer-->>User: OAuth callback with token
    User->>OAuthProxy: OAuth token via callback<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    OAuthProxy->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>verb:get resource:notebooks<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>OAuthProxy: Allowed
    OAuthProxy->>Notebook: Forward request<br/>HTTP localhost:8888
    Notebook-->>OAuthProxy: Response
    OAuthProxy-->>Router: Response (TLS)
    Router-->>User: Notebook UI

    Note over User, Notebook: Flow 3: Non-OAuth Mode (Simplified)

    User->>Router: GET https://{notebook-route}<br/>TLS 1.2+ (Edge termination)
    Router->>Notebook: Forward to Service<br/>HTTP 8888/TCP
    Notebook-->>Router: Response
    Router-->>User: Notebook UI
